        "action": "Introduce a Dog Tax",
        "additional_details": "By \u2018taxing\u2019 owning a dog, given time, would reduce demand hence the social benefits of:-\r\nFewer illegal dog breeders.\r\nFewer attacks. \r\nLess crowding in abandoned dog homes.\r\nReduced dog importing.\r\nReduced dog fouling providing a more pleasant and cleaner environment on our pavements, in our parks, public pathways and countryside.\r\nReduced \u2018noise pollution\u2019.    \r\nFunding for improved control, \u2018policing\u2019 of dogs and creating jobs.",
        "background": "Introduce a \u2018dog tax\u2019 based on the German model. Dependant on the dog type and local authorities, German\u2019s can pay annually in excess of 800e per dog. \r\nThere is an increasing, estimated 8.7 million dogs in the Uk which is spiralling out of control.",
